From White:

A-H from Queenside to Kingside
1-8 from White's side

8 r  n  b  q  k  b  n  r
7
6
5
4
3
2 p  p  p  p  p  p  p  p
1 r  n  b  q  k  b  n  r
  A  B  C  D  E  F  G  H


Piece types:

Not specified: pawn

R: rook
N: knight
B: bishop
Q: queen
K: king

Movement:

(Character's uppercase letter) + (If capturing, type x) + (Destination)

eg.
Pawn moves to c5: c5
Pawn on rank 4 captures piece on c5: 4xc5
Bishop captures piece on e5: Bxe5

Disambiguation:
If two or more identical pieces can move to the same square, the moving piece is specified by:

1: File of departure (Letter/ Column)
2: Rank of departure (Number/ Row)
3: Both file and rank (in rare cases)

En passant:
(capturing pawn's file of departure) + x + (destination square)
eg. pawn on e5 captures pawn on d5 with en passant: exd6

Pawn Promotion:
Indicate piece to be promoted at the end of notation
eg. e8Q

Castling:
0-0 for Kingside
0-0-0 for Queenside

Check:
Append '+' to the end of move input

Checkmate:
Append '#' to the end of move input
